EmailTemplate.subject: Live Different Builds: Mexico 2014
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hi {!Contact.FirstName}!
We would like to welcome you to the Live Different Build team. My name is Jenn and I am an Administrator with our Live Different Builds. We are looking forward to meeting you in person and having you along on this trip as we work together to make a difference! This Live Different Build is not only going to be an incredible opportunity to make a tangible difference for people that need it most, but to also have your entire world view changed!
Please read over the following to help you prepare for your trip:
Secure your spot on the trip:
Your first $300 of your fundraising goal needs to be made within 2 weeks of your registration. Use your Canada Helps Page for making, entering and requesting donations or payments related to your trip. You can share (email, Facebook, etc.) your Canada Helps Page with any potential donors so they can donate online to your Live Different Build project (to help meet your fundraising goal).
The following forms are attached to this email:
Consent Forms - Please scan and email this back to me within 2 weeks of registration. Presentation Letter - This a great tool for fund raising. Present this letter to potential donors and businesses when looking for donations towards your trip. It gives an explanation of who Live Different is and what Live Different Build is all about. It's also a good idea to include a letter from yourself explaining why you want to participate on a Live Different Build and what you hope to accomplish. Packing List - No idea what to pack? Read this form and it will remind you of all the little things that will make your trip and travels more comfortable.
These forms are only for adults (18 years of age as of January 1st, 2014):
Criminal Record Check (through mybackcheck) - If you are 18 years of age (as of January 1st, 2014), you will be required to obtain a criminal record check. Please obtain one through the email link I will send you. Child Protection Policy - The Child Protection Policy is for volunteers over 18 years of age (as of January 1, 2014) to read before each trip they attend. It is our policy on what is appropriate behaviour when dealing with minors and the steps that we take to protect them. It's important that you take the time to read this from beginning to end. Child Protection Policy Agreement - Once you have read the above Child Protection Policy, please sign the agreement and send it in with your next payment. This can also be scanned and emailed, or faxed to me as we do not need the original copy.
Booking your flights:
If you haven't already checked out your trip page, please do so this week so you can become familiar with our trip itinerary and start booking your flights: http://livedifferent.com/hero-holiday/trips/mx-2014-new-years-public-trip
Airport: San Diego - Airport Code: SAN Arrival: December 27, 2014 Departure: January 5, 2015
Forwarding the Itinerary
Once you have booked your flights, please forward me your flight itinerary. We need to know when you are arriving and departing so that we can arrange airport shuttles.
Upon Arrival:
All volunteers fly into the San Diego Airport and our staff will pick them up. Once all our volunteers have arrived we spend a night at the Best Western hotel in Chula Vista, CA. As a group, the next day, we drive down to Vicente Guerrero, Mexico. It's approximately 4 hours south of San Diego, along the Baja coast of California, but with stops it will take around 5 hours to get there.
Pick up and drop off: Once you have booked your flights, please forward me your trip itinerary and I can add you to our bus shuttle. When you arrive at the San Diego airport, our staff will be at the gate wearing a Live Different t-shirt and holding a Live Different Build sign, and you will then be taken to the Best Western hotel for the night.
Please keep in mind that there are other volunteers on this trip, so our staff will be doing airport shuttles all day, which is one reason why we don't leave for Mexico until the following day.
After we drop off the volunteers at the airport on their last day, they get on their flight and they're on their own from there on. All the volunteers can be picked up on the other side by their parents or other family members.
Accommodations: We own our own comfortable and clean homes on a gated property in the community of Zapata, Mexico. We have full time staff that live down in Mexico all year round that help host all our trips. All of our volunteers will be staying on our property while we are in Mexico.
Transportation: We own all of our own buses, vans, and vehicles that are used to transport our volunteers from San Diego to Mexico, and from our homes to the communities we will be working in. The drivers are staff that have experience driving in Mexico, as well as the legal documents to drive these registered vehicles.
Communities We Work In: Since 2006, we have developed very strong relationships with the communities that we work in. The communities know Live Different very well and we feel very safe at all times while working on our building sites.
Work Site Safety: We require all volunteers to bring closed toed shoes, a hat/bandana, waterbottle, sunglasses, sunscreen, and leather work gloves. This ensures that volunteers are as equipped for handling equipment on the job sites.
Area We Live In: The area that we live and work in is a rural area that survives on farming. It is extremely safe and quiet, volunteers often feel safer in Mexico than they do in their own neighborhoods in Canada.
Vaccinations and Medications: We do not require that any of our volunteers receive any vaccinations or medications to go to any of the countries that we work in. But, we do suggest that every volunteer visit their family doctor or local medical clinic and decide on your own about taking any medications or vaccinations prior to the trip.
Map from US to MX: Here is a map of our drive from the Best Western in Chula Vista, CA to our home in Zapata (a few minutes away from Vicente Guerrero): https://maps.google.ca/maps?q=%4030.771699,-116.006355&oe=utf-8&aq=t&client=firefox-a&ie=UTF-8&hl=en.
Excursion Day (trip specific): There are a few options for the excursion day that our staff will decide on closer to the date of the trip (volcano hike, beach day, etc.). Whatever is decided on, please be aware that there are many factors on our staff deciding where to takes our groups (depending on whether, and multiple safety precautions).
Contact during a trip between volunteers and Canada: There is wifi at the house that all volunteers to use 24/7 and are able to skype with their family members. We also have a facebook page that we update every day to keep family and friends informed. All of our staff have cell phones on them at all times and we also have a land line. We will be emailing everyone all of the emergency contact information before the trip starts.
Photos and Videos:
Here are some photos and videos from our past Live Different Build trips if you would like to use them for your fundraising needs: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/3wke2n7mm37rg7e/E0VsZOT3q8
Other Important Information: Check out our Live Different Facebook page! There are photos, blogs and videos from our most recent trips. It's a great resource to help you prepare for your trip: http://www.facebook.com/pages/Live-Different/189864944417296.
You can also visit our FAQ section on our website as it is a great resource. http://www.livedifferent.com/faqs
Please e-mail me back with any questions or concerns you may have. I look forward to answering them for you!
Sincerley,
Jenn Digiandomenico
